<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-78-1098 </DOCNO><TEXT>The annual public power report on innovative developments suggests thatutilities are finding a variety of ways to approach common problems.It also demonstrates the acceptance of the 5-E Test which asks if a solutionis efficient, effective, equitable, economic, and environmentally acceptable.The diversity of innovations indicates that local utilities are stressingflexibility and focusing on the use in seeking least cost results. Thereport covers 38 classifications of innovations, which range from advancedgeneration technologies to renewable energy sources, integrated systems,rate management, and waste heat recovery. A summary paragraph describeswhat is happening at public power plants under each category.</TEXT></DOC>